11/05/2003
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Bosnia and Herzegovina's (BiH) Prime Minister Adnan Terzic wrapped up a two-day official visit to Serbia-Montenegro on Friday (9 May). 
Terzic met with senior representatives of the local authorities in Belgrade and Podgorica, re-affirming the two countries' willingness to improve bilateral relations, regional co-operation and joint actions for combating organised crime. 
Meeting in Podgorica Friday, Terzic and Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic agreed that co-operation between the countries should be expanded in the view of the common EU integration perspectives. 
(Tanjug, BBC, HINA - 10/05/03; PBS BiH - 09/05/03)
